Personal Finance Manager
Project Overview

The Personal Finance Manager is a Python-based command-line application designed to help users efficiently track and manage their personal expenses. Built using object-oriented programming principles, this project emphasizes modularity, maintainability, and real-world applicability. Users can record expenses, generate category-wise summaries, view monthly reports, and back up or restore their data. The application stores all expense records in CSV files for easy persistence and retrieval. With robust input validation, comprehensive error handling, and a user-friendly interactive menu, this tool demonstrates practical Python skills while offering a functional solution for everyday financial management.

Features

Add, view, and manage personal expenses

Generate category-wise summaries of expenses

Generate monthly expense reports

Backup and restore expense data

Input validation and error handling for reliable usage

Modular, maintainable code structure for easy future extensions

Setup Instructions

Clone the repository to your local machine:

git clone <your-repo-url>


Navigate to the project directory:

cd PersonalFinanceManager


Install required Python dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt


Run the main application:

python main.py

Usage

Upon running the application, users will see a menu with the following options:

Add a new expense

View all expenses

View category-wise summary

Generate monthly report

Backup data

Restore backup

Exit

Users can interact with the menu by entering the corresponding number. All expenses are saved to a CSV file (data/expenses.csv) and can be backed up or restored as needed.
